      "name": "Charles Kawczynski"
    },
    "body": "If a contributor manually merges a PR that increments the reference counter, then it doesn't go through the `\"gh-readonly-queue/main/\"` prefixed-branch, and data is not properly moved onto central. The result is that any subsequent PR will seem to be behavior changing even though it may not be.\r\n\r\nThis PR should make our reproducibility tests more robust to this situation (so long we run CI on main).",
